Subject: [PATCH v19 08/19] tracing/fprobe: Enable fprobe events with CONFIG_DYNAMIC_FTRACE_WITH_ARGS
Date: Mon, 11 Nov 2024 00:50:23 +0900
Message-ID: <173125382335.172790.9364683419794043855.stgit@devnote2>
X-Mailer: git-send-email 2.43.0
In-Reply-To: <173125372214.172790.6929368952404083802.stgit@devnote2>
References: <173125372214.172790.6929368952404083802.stgit@devnote2>
User-Agent: StGit/0.19
Precedence: bulk
X-Mailing-List: linux-arch@vger.kernel.org
List-Id: <linux-arch.vger.kernel.org>
List-Subscribe: <mailto:linux-arch+subscribe@vger.kernel.org>
List-Unsubscribe: <mailto:linux-arch+unsubscribe@vger.kernel.org>
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset="utf-8"
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

From: Masami Hiramatsu (Google) <mhiramat@kernel.org>

Allow fprobe events to be enabled with CONFIG_DYNAMIC_FTRACE_WITH_ARGS.
With this change, fprobe events mostly use ftrace_regs instead of pt_regs.
Note that if the arch doesn't enable HAVE_FTRACE_REGS_HAVING_PT_REGS,
fprobe events will not be able to be used from perf.

Signed-off-by: Masami Hiramatsu (Google) <mhiramat@kernel.org>
---
 Changes in v9:
  - Copy store_trace_entry_data() as store_fprobe_entry_data() for
    fprobe.
 Chagnes in v3:
  - Use ftrace_regs_get_return_value().
 Changes in v2:
  - Define ftrace_regs_get_kernel_stack_nth() for
    !CONFIG_HAVE_REGS_AND_STACK_ACCESS_API.
 Changes from previous series: Update against the new series.
---
